description: Numbers n such that 20^n - 19^n is prime.
comments: Terms n > 1000 may correspond to (unproven) strong pseudoprimes 20^n - 19^n.
author: _Mike Oakes_, May 18 2001, May 19 2001
extensions: Three more terms (18661, 79621 and 81649) found by Jean-Louis Charton in February and March 2011 corresponding to probable primes with 24279, 103590 and 106228 digits.
